                18</ref>)</enactingFormula><sourceNote>(Enacting provision omitted—<ref href="/hk/2012/er2">E.R. 2 of
            2012</ref>)<marker role="blank-line"></marker><marker role="blank-line"></marker></sourceNote><commencementNote>[5 November 1993]</commencementNote><sourceNote>(Format changes—<ref href="/hk/2012/er2">E.R. 2 of 2012</ref>)</sourceNote><section id="ID_1438403198153_003" name="s1" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2012-08-02" status="operational" temporalId="s1"><num value="1">1.</num><heading>Fees</heading><subsection id="ID_1438412514003_028" name="1" temporalId="s1_1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content>The fees payable for the purposes of <ref>section 18(1)(a)</ref> of the Ordinance shall be the fees prescribed in the <ref>Schedule</ref>.</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1438412514003_036" name="2" temporalId="s1_2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content>Where a licence is granted or renewed for a period of less than 12 months, the fees payable under subsection (1) shall be the sum obtained by dividing the amount of the prescribed fee by the number of days in the year when the licence is granted or renewed and multiplying the result by the total number of days in the months for which the licence is granted or renewed, as the case may be.</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1438412514019_005" name="3" temporalId="s1_3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content>The appointed public officer may waive, remit, reduce or refund the whole or
                any part of a fee for which provision is made under this Regulation.<inline class="width_3"> </inline><sourceNote>(<ref href="/hk/2011/17">17 of 2011 s.
                        28</ref>)</sourceNote><marker role="section-break"></marker></content></subsection></section><section id="ID_1438403198169_001" name="s2" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2012-08-02" status="operational" temporalId="s2"><num value="2">2.</num><heading>Issue of a duplicate of a licence</heading><content>The appointed public officer may on application in writing to him by a licensee, showing cause to his satisfaction, and on payment of the prescribed fee, issue to the licensee a duplicate of his licence.</content><sourceNote>(<ref href="/hk/2011/17">17 of 2011 s. 28</ref>)</sourceNote></section><schedule id="ID_1438403198169_003" name="sch0" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2012-08-02" status="operational" temporalId="sch0"><num value="0">Schedule</num><note class="align_right" role="crossReferences" type="inline">[<ref href="/hk/cap435B/s1">s.
